-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
README
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Scripts for building sigrok and its dependencies natively on MSYS2, targeting
the UCRT64 (GCC) and CLANG64 (Clang/LLVM) environments.


Requirements
------------

 - Docker (for sigrok-msys2-docker)
 - or a native MSYS2 installation (for sigrok-native-msys2)


Building with Docker (recommended for CI)
------------------------------------------

The sigrok-msys2-docker script runs the entire build inside the MSYS2 Docker
container (ghcr.io/msys2/msys2-docker-experimental) on a Linux host.
No Windows installation is required.

  $ ./sigrok-msys2-docker UCRT64     # Build with GCC (UCRT64)
  $ ./sigrok-msys2-docker CLANG64    # Build with Clang/LLVM (CLANG64)

Output is placed in the output/ subdirectory:
  - sigrok-msys2-release.zip  (portable release archive)
  - sigrok-installer.exe      (NSIS Windows installer)


Building natively on MSYS2
--------------------------

Start an "MSYS2 UCRT64" or "MSYS2 CLANG64" shell. Do NOT use the "MSYS2 MSYS"
shell.

First, install all required packages:

  $ ./sigrok-native-msys2 prepare

Then build:

  $ ./sigrok-native-msys2


Files
-----

  sigrok-native-msys2
    The build script that runs inside MSYS2. Handles package installation,
    building all sigrok components, gathering DLLs, and creating the NSIS
    installer.

  sigrok-msys2-docker
    Docker wrapper that runs sigrok-native-msys2 inside the MSYS2 Docker
    container on a Linux host.

  sigrok-installer.nsi
    NSIS installer script for the combined PulseView + sigrok-cli installer.

  0001-Allow-building-with-MSYS2-use-dynamic-libs.patch
    Patch for PulseView to use dynamic linking on MSYS2.

  0002-libsigrok-COFF-section-ordering-and-dllexport.patch
    Patch for libsigrok to support both GCC and Clang/lld on Windows:
    - Uses COFF section $-suffix ordering for the driver list, avoiding
      the ld -r partial link step (which lld does not support for COFF).
    - Adds __declspec(dllexport) for proper symbol visibility with Clang.
    - Removes SR_API from template class (incompatible with dllexport).
